column23: What the heck is up with the guy who makes fresh guac at the tables ringing a bicycle bell attached to the his push cart as he walks around the restaurant? I'm not kidding. Tacky and annoying.   My family and I ate here a few days ago and will not be returning. We've been several times and sometimes is very good, sometimes it's average. The salsas (mild, hot and extra hot) are good sometimes but just plain boring other times. I'm completely baffled by the comments saying the salsa is awesome. The only reason we have returned is because our kids ask to go there. I guess they are easily impressed. ;-) We won't go back, though. Our food was boring. I can make food of the same quality at home and I'm not even a very good cook. It was bland and they do not put any garnish on the dinners we've ordered.  American Mexican food almost always has at least a small amount of lettuce, tomato and possibly sour cream and guac. One of the items in my dinner was a tostada. It consisted of the shell, beans and cheese; that's it. Umm, no. Can you say cheap-o restaurant? Plus, my tostada was completely soggy. I sent it back along with the rest of my dinner. I'm from Arizona, Mexican food is my favorite and I've eaten in hundreds of times. I've never been served a tostada like that. Gross.   I had an issue with my meal as mentioned above and when the server, who was very polite, could not resolve it we asked to speak to the manager. This manager is just not customer service centered at all and proceeded to argue with me over something that she was clearly in the wrong about. I've had a bad experience with this same manager in the past as well. She should not be working in a restaurant. I was nice to her. She was a jerk to me both times.   Do yourself a favor and eat elsewhere.

Delicious margaritas & food! The bartender isn't the friendliest but he makes a mean margarita (order the top shelf- totally worth it!). The servers are excellent and very nice. Yummy enchiladas, cheese dip, & the spicy salsa is the best!
This is my favorite Mexican place in Fort Mill. I love that they bring spicy and mild salsa to the table. Tasty food, good portions, great lunch prices, and friendly staff, what more could you want!

column23: I have been here many times for lunch and have gotten the chicken fajitas every time. I normally like variety, but these are just too good. The only negative is I wish they provided more spicy options. I have had them make dishes spicer and it was fantastic, but they charge extra. Otherwise, this has become my favorite place to eat in the area.

This is probably the worst Mexican food I have ever had. When ordered queso first and it was watery and strangely solid white...no chilis, etc. Once the entrees were served they smell coming from them was strange and off putting. My daughter and I couldn't eat more than a bite to try and see if we could push past the smell. Mexican is our favorite and we have been to more Mexican restaurants than any other type of restaurant. This place really disappointed.

column23: Mediocre food and drink plus pricey for a strip mall Mexican place. Waiter had the personality of a piece of wood and I noticed this with others too. Not rude just not there.

Very good wait staff. Friendly & quick.  I had fajitas - sizzled when brought to table . Son had enchiladas verde - he wolfed it down. Husband had pollo pablano - he loved it. Salsa is tasty - either mild or spicy

Do yourself a favor and turn around and leave! This place SUUUUCKS! I tried to be objective after reading all the negative feedback, but every negative review was right on. It's too Bad because It's close to home and in a really good location. I got a manager to come to our table and told her that we just wanted to leave. My wife's order was wrong (no chicken inside a wrap) and my chicken enchiladas were acidic, runny green sauce that looked like it was poured on top right out of a can and I had to douse the rice with salt and pepper. The waiter had a look of frustration like he was used to unhappy customers. The staff and the manager were friendly enough and the manager was very apologetic and didn't argue with me about my dislike of the quality of the food and my refusal to pay. We got up and left and will not return.

column23: I'm very surprised by all the negative comments. I've always had friendly and fast service. Their fish tacos are so yummy and the soups are delicious!
Great chips but the salsa is a little watery. Try the Fluotas sp?

I'm usually pretty long-winded with my reviews, but this place can be summed up as average.   It's your standard Mexican restaurant with colorful decor and Mexican mariache music playing. We went for an early dinner on a Sunday, and the place was just a little under halfway full with a few outside tables taken, too.  The margaritas are huge (even the medium), and the chips and salsa are free... and fine. The fella got a taco\/burrito combo, and he said it was good. I got the fajitas carnitas, and they were fine. Our waitress was young and sweet but maybe just a little forgetful.  Charanda isn't going to wow you, but it isn't going to disappoint you either.

This place is vastly improved and is probably the best Mexican in the area now. Try the Burrito Taxano. It has BACON. EVERYTHING is good with bacon.

column23: Went with co-workers last week and overall it was a positive experience (3.5).  It was a co-workers birthday and they gave us a little dessert (enough for all but one of us...but hey, it's free), and they put a big sombrero on him while singing, a nice touch!   I ordered the shrimp fajitas. There was only really 5-6 shrimp on a huge bed of onions (and some red bell pepper sprinkled in). On the plus side the shrimp tasted great and were cooked nicely. I also really liked the rice it was served with.    I  thought it was weird that my co-worker and I ordered the same thing but they only brought one container of tortillas. I would rather have had my own as it's kind of gross to put your hands on something someone else is eating.   The atmosphere is nice, it is clean (smelled-strongly of cleaner)..but I am okay with that.   I would return if I were in the area.

column23: Went in and sat in the bar area. The bartender was also our waitress. She immediately took our drink orders and brought us chips and salsa. We ordered a couple margaritas and some queso.  The house margarita needs work, tastes like OJ with tequila.  However, the frozen Mango margarita was delicious!  We ordered a combination plate and carnitas. The enchilada and burrito were not very good, the enchilada sauce was very runny with virtually no flavor.  The poblano was really good with chicken.  The carnitas were not pulled apart, the meat came in large chunks, no biggie, had great flavor.  The food overall was ok, satisfied the craving for Mexican food, but not great for a $40 dinner.  However, the service was great! The bartender and staff were on top of taking orders, delivering and picking up plates! Great job on service!

column23: Absolutely HORRIBLE!!!!  The bad experience started with a rude hostess followed up with an inpolite waitress who did not know the menu and topped off with a horrible meal.  Within ten minutes of leaving I was vomiting and I was sick for another 6-8 hours after that.  I would have to say this was in my top five of Horrible eating experiences.  Taco bell would have been an upgrade to my experience here.  I will never return and would not recommend it to anyone unless they were my enemy nah not even them! :( :( :( :( :(  Thats 5 frownies!

With all of the stellar Mexican restaurants in Pineville and Charlotte, Charanda just doesn't measure up. I'd much rather drive a little farther to get better service and food.  In my opinion, prices are high compared to other places I frequent. My biggest complaint, though, is about the service. I seem to always get the same waitress every time I go there: a young blonde girl. She does not need to be a server. She always seems frazzled, does not regularly refill drinks or salsa, and generally neglects her tables all while seeming like she cannot handle the stress.   Their salsa is awesome, though!

In town to visit family and somebody suggested take out from this place.  I shared an order of chicken fajitas con mi hijo. Really not very good, small portion and the didn't include the flour tortillas. The salsa was a notch below Pace.

column23: We stopped by last night for appetizers & drinks, hopefully outside at one of the tables with umbrellas. I dropped the wife off at the door to secure a table while I parked the car. Unfortunately, she came to the car stating there was an hour wait even though several tables were empty on the patio. She stated the hostess told her they did not have enough servers and were unable to seat people in those empty tables. We let without eating or waiting. We also noticed several other parties leaving without waiting.
Finally tried this place! Not too shabby. My meal was delish. The prices are great too. The service was a bit slow but very courteous. I will be back for sure!

column23: This is definitely a "one and done" for us. We were excited to have a Mexican restaurant move in to the shopping center by Lowe's Home Improvement.  The hostesses were not friendly, did not ask if we wanted to sit indoors or out, and although the restaurant was mostly empty, took us to a booth next to the kitchen door in the bar (what I would consider one of the worst tables in the house). When I ask for a different table, she wasn't very happy about it.  We were seated and given menus, our server (who was nice but poorly trained) took our drink orders. He brought our waters, chips and salsa (and he mixed up which was the mild and which was the spicy salsa) but it was a good 10 minutes before our drinks from the bar arrived. We requested napkins (at this point we didn't have any napkins or silverware). We had to ask for napkins 2-3 times before we got some.  Our food was delivered on screaming hot plates (definitely had been sitting under the warmer for a while. My Chili Pablanos were soggy because they had been sitting around for a while. We still had no silverware at this point. Again we asked for it and finally received the pre-rolled cheap silverware in a napkin.  Our server was fairly attentive but not great. As we were leaving the restaurant, there was a large group of folks at the hostess stand waiting to be seated and the three hostesses who had been working earlier in the evening were no where to be found.  Definitely will not be going there again!!!!  As we drove by Taco Bell on the way home, I commented to my husband that we could have gotten an equal quality meal there for much less money.

column23: Mediocre service was the highlight.  Seriously.  Let's start at the beginning.  We were seated in a booth, and given menus.  This wouldn't be at all odd, but my preschool aged kids were also given menus, and not the kind you can color on--adult menus.  Odd, but you don't lose any points for that.  After sitting for what seemed like a really long time, we had the opportunity to order beverages--the kids had chocolate milk which arrived in a styro-cup with a lid intact, but no straws.  We had to actually ask for straws, and then watched as our confused waitress visited every table in our section straws in hand, trying to figure out who needed them before solving the puzzle.  The food came and it was atrocious to put it mildly.  I burned my elbow against my plate, which would have been somewhat my fault, if I didn't have a taco salad.  The lettuce was hot, the tomatoes were hot, the cheese was hot.  I suspect they cooked the whole thing, plate and all in an oven.  I might have gotten past it, if the beef weren't swimming in soup at the bottom of the soggy taco shell.    I also ordered chicken tacos, which had dry flavorless meat, cheese which tasted like processed mozzarella string cheese, and nothing else.  Bleh.  I didn't finish either dish.  My wife ordered steak ranchero tacos, which came with a decent presentation, but my wife said they were also flavorless.  She offered me her last taco, but I'll take her word for it, that it was bland.  After trying to coax my kids into eating their quesadillas, I decided to take a bite myself, and wanted to cry.  Picture melted string cheese encasing a frozen chicken strip.  Next time we are craving decent Mexican, (which is almost always, since we are California transplants), we are driving the extra 10 minutes to Tequila in Rock Hill.  The place looks like a dive inside and out, but the food and service has never disappointed.

I will never eat at this location again. I've eaten there a few times and every single time the food has been OK but not great and the service has been nothing short of deplorable. The waitstaff is grossly inattentive and rude. They treat elderly people like crap.

column23: First visit to this one and will be our last. Took forever for our waitress to come take our drink order so we went ahead and gave our food order. I ordered extra red sauce with my meal but got none. My husband had to ask for the shells that were suppose to come with his meal. Our waitress never came by after we got our meal to check on us. I asked for a box to take my leftovers home and asked again for the extra red sauce, we were charged extra for it. I have eaten at the Newport one and it is way better. By the way they were not busy. on

Service was questionable at best. One our meals was not correct when brought to the table. One of the waiters wanted argue vs fix the order.  Our other meal (fajitas) was brought with out the tortillas...took 10 mins for them to be brought to the table while the food became cool.  They comp a meal but even the manager did not apologize. It's been a long time since I've experienced anything like it.

I ordered a beef taco, chicken enchilada, and a beef tostada. Everyone understands there is sauce on the enchilada, so it seems like they might have separated that from the other two items, especially the hand-held taco. Instead, it arrived all on one plate, with the saucy enchilada in the middle. Picking up the taco without getting enchilada sauce all over my hands would have been impossible. They were nice to bring me another taco and take the sauced one away.   Also, it was my first time here and no one explained the fresh guacamole cart upfront. When it hit my table, I wasn't sure if it was complimentary or if I would be charged for it, so I passed.  The tip container on the container was right at eye level. Couldn't miss that.   The enchilada was nicely seasoned, but the chicken was a bit on the dry side. The ground beef on the taco and tostada was decent, if a little greasy, and it needed salt IMO. Chips were good, as was the salsa.   I might try this place again when I am in town.

column23: Over priced, poor service, don't order margaritas. We have eaten at other Charandas so felt comfortable taking friends here. Huge mistake. Wait staff barely spoke English so we tried to order by number. My husband ordered #18 on their menu. After bringing food for 4 of us they brought him #8 from the menu instead of 18. When he told them that wasn't what he ordered, they argued with him. All 4 of us tried to back him up. He never got the correct food and cancelled his order entirely after the other 4 of us finished eating before he even got his meal.  We were charged $14 each for Margaritas that tasted like nothing but straight lime juice. We ordered a shot of Grand Marnier to try to make the nasty Margarita drinkable. We were charged $10 for a shot of Gran Marnier. Horrible  service, crappy over priced drinks. We will NEVER go back. They screwed everything up and could have cared less.
Very disappointing they do not offer single steak  tacos, you have to buy an entire platter that's just way more than anyone can eat for dinner. Also a little pricy and service is mediocre at best.

I would say that this is standard to sub-standard Mexican food that you would find in a standard Mexican restaurant, but it was not great or even good by any means.  I definitely would not eat here again.
The chicken fajita nachos here are so good! Ill be back to get them for sure. The service was a bit slow and there was an issue with one of the orders but they resolved it fairly quickly.

I was very excited to have a Mexican restaurant so close to where I work. Sadly, this is not the place for me. The best thing about the place is the bartender. He is friendly and attentive. Maybe if he ran the place, it would be better? As for the rest, the service is slow, the staff rude and the food bland and flavorless with weird tasting cheese sauce. Sorry Charanda's. I will continue my search for good Mexican food in the South elsewhere.

column23: This place is fantastic! The service was quick and very friendly, and the food was awesome. The menu goes beyond typical Mexican fare, and includes some unique twists. The Steak Tampiquena was incredible, and I would recommend any one of their dishes that has the poblano pepper cream sauce.
Tablemade guacamole was delicious! I had a vegetarian combo that was also very good. Location was a bit dark and could have been cleaner, but the service and food was very good.

I have eaten here quite a few times and the food is good. The 2 stars is because they no longer have limes!(trying to get a response) I ordered a margarita (ultimate which was very good) and when I asked for a lime the bartender said they had stopped ordering them because they were too expensive! Now granted this didn't make or break my meal but that was one of the strangest things I have heard. It wasn't like it was $2 margarita night ($9 to be exact) Hopefully someone in management will see this and respond. If you like a lime with your margarita or your Mexican beer you may want to pass until they they make a better business decision

Not a bad Mexican place in Fort Mill. My goto spot is Don Pedro in Rivergate, but we decided to try something new. I thought this was on par with the Don. Its a typical menu, but slightly different. The sauces especially were different. I had a Mexican beer, enchilada's with the unique sauce. We had cheese dip which was good. Overall, a solid place. Staff was nice. I would definitely come back if in the area.

column23: DELICIOUS!!! We've been here two times and the food was quick, hot, fresh, and delicious!! Our server the first time was a jerk, but our guy yesterday was friendly and attentive. The chips were hot, crisp and fresh. They came with two salsas, mild and spicy.  The only complaint I have is they give it to you in such little dishes, but they do refill. We had the lunch specials. Baldie had the beef burrito and taco combo with rice. I ordered steak and cheese with onions in a flour tortilla. Omg, this bitch has the most tender, juicy beef, grilled onions and cheese all melted, oozing and melding together with all the juices from the steak. I'm droolin ova here now!! That came with rice and pico de gallo on lettuce.  I needed some refried beans, man!! All that, plus 2 sweet teas and it cost it's 20 bucks!' Ole, bitches!!

column23: Been here a few times now. It's the epitome of a 3 star place. It's good, not great. Starting with the atmosphere, it's your typical Mexican restaurant decor but maybe a little better with granite counter tops and nicer bathrooms. The service is friendly and lightning fast. The salsas (regular and hot) are water thin. I prefer thicker salsas but I occasionally like the thin kind too. These ones are average at best. Same with the chips. My wife and I both ordered the chicken enchiladas verde and they are good.  They also have a good children's menu for the little ones.  If you're looking for quick, tasty Mexican food and you're near one of their many locations, it's worth trying out. I just wouldn't go out of my way to get there.

We came here today for a lunch service and sadly, won't be returning. My favorite part of the meal was the chips and hot salsa.   I ordered the chicken tortilla soup with a chicken taco side for a dollar extra while the bf ordered the lunch quesadilla. I have to admit, I could not get through the chicken tortilla soup. My first issue, was the enormous glob of sour cream that was thrown on to my soup making it somewhat inedible. I scooped it out and attempted to eat again. I was sad to find that there were no veggies or beans in my soup, it only consisted of chicken broth, rice, bland shredded chicken, and soggy tortilla strips. 5 minutes in, I gave up, couldn't get past the soggy tortilla chips which was similar in consistency to soggy cereal. Bleh. The taco was also not appetizing.   The server was nice but she wasn't as attentive as she should have been. It took forever to get a water refill. I will not be returning to Charanda in Fort Mill.

column23: I've eaten at the restaurant off of Dave Lyle and the one off of Hwy 160. I just wasn't impressed with their food.

The food here is far better than your run of the mill Mexican restaurant and the portions are generous. Everything I've tried has been excellent, including the drinks. In my three visits the service has been prompt and courteous.

Very poor.       Starting with the host... He would have been just as welcoming if he just pointed at the table that he assigned us to. I can not say that he seated us. He merely assigned us a seat and walked away.       Our server greeted us by setting a basket of nacho chip crumbs on the table, stood in front of us and waited for us to tell him what we wanted to drink. After a ten minute wait for our waters the man proceeded to take our food order in the same fashion, by just standing there... Literally, not a single word was spoken.       The food got to the table on scalding hot plates that were obviously microwaved. My burritos were floating in water and melted cheese. Absolutely disgusting.      I can't justify wasting anymore time on a review for this place. This establishment was given a star from me only because it is the minimum.

Even though i would mostly agree with most of the other reviews, we have still been there several different times mainly on Friday nights.  Sometimes with small groups other times with just the family.  This place is so up and down when it comes to service, you never know what your going to get, but i can say that we have never had anything bad off of the menu but just be prepared to remind them that you still need something and you should be ok.

Drink specials,  good sauces, big drinks,  and superb service make this a great restaurant. Everything we ordered was delicioso. Tacos de Asada come with a spicy green salsa that I want multiple bottles of for Christmas presents!!! Super Yum!

column23: Ok...I have been here before for take out and usually the people are very friendly.  I called for take out and when I got there, the door was locked.  When I called to explain that the door was locked, I got no response. After that call finally the door was opened by someone who definitely didn't apologize or even explain.  Then asked how many not even looking at me.  I stated I was picking up an order, then she said go over to the bar -and literally walked away.  Wow....bad enough I wasn't feeling well and picking up some soup for myself, but to be treated like I was "bothering" them is another thing. Was I really going to give them my $?    When I ordered, I specifically asked if the soup was a good portion. Said yes, yes. good.  Uh ok....the container wasn't even all the way full & the chips taste a bit stale.  The mild salsa that was given, not even half full in this small container.  They weren't very friendly-the only one who smiled was the man behind the bar.    The soup is good and ordered a side as well.  The portions are not what I would call standard or even decent.  I wish El Cancun was still open, sad they closed, because when you ordered any food, you got what you paid for!  Looks like I will be searching for another Mexican restaurant.

It isn't my favorite Mexican place, but it is the best in the Fort Mill area.  Margarita's were so sweet two of the four of us started feeling it in our stomach's.  Atmosphere is above average, food is alright and service was good.

column23: We really enjoyed the fresh food here, very good service as well.  Love the fresh guacamole made at your table.  Everything here is amazing,  which explains the crowd every weekend.   We went on an off night during the week and sat right down.  I had a Mexican shrimp dish that was spicy, unexpected but delicious.   The chips and salsa were also very good, we ate through them and needed a refill.  Chicken dishes are also very good, a must try if your looking for great authentic Mexican cuisine.

column23: Not bad just not good. If you grew up here you think it's great. If you ever lived in Texas this couldn't make it to a one star. What the hell pulled pork sucks in Texas. Just have to set realistic expectations.

Let me start by saying service here was pretty impeccable. Not MIA and not over-bearing, a good mix. Refills on the waters\/ soft-drinks and, my favorite, the salsa. Very friendly servers.   The food is pretty decent (from what I can tell). You won't be disappointed with the Fajitas or a Taco Salad. However, think twice about the Quesadillas. Unless your into a Quesadilla SOUP you may not be thrilled with this dish. The runny, "cheese dip" cheese is like a pure swimming pool on your plate. I had to eat the entire Quesadilla with a fork and knife.   But yeah, other dishes look good. I'd be back.

column23: Great place ...next time I will request  patio table. I had Arroz.con Camarones.  (SHRIMP W\/RICE)... good flavor. The right size.  Very tasty and also we ordered  fish tacos  perfect. The only problem was no more space.for desserts.

Great location, terrible food. The 10$ special maragirta was friggin nasty, wife wouldn't drink it. Chi I was almost ok, but very dry and overcooked. My burrito had marinara sauce on it, I swear.. It was marinara tomato sauce. Waiters were all tools.. Totally will drive to Monroe or huntersville for Azteca.. Avoid this place!!
Good food. Mild and regular salsa served w chips. Large variety of margaritas. Standard (Americanized) Mexican dishes.

column23: We just discovered this place...  it's the best Mexican food around!!  Fresh, tasty ingredients, friendly service (thanks Mario!), reasonable prices, generous portions...  this place is what you're looking for, I'm telling you  :-)
Really great food, good service, extremely affordable prices. Went there for lunch and had a very good experience. I will definitely go back again.

column23: I love this charandas! Always great service  and great food! Very friendly staff as well

I've gone a few times for lunch and I've had a good experience every time. They have fast service and the food is yummy. I really like their complementary salsa and chips and the chimichungas are delish!

Had a nice Fajita lunch here recently. The restaurant is clean and well run.  Food is served hot and prompt. Staff is very pleasant.  The food is good, but not above average. They have a large bar area and seem to be a local favorite.  Very convenient to I-77.  I would stop here again.
Wow!  Made to order guacamole at your table?!! Fresh, delicious dishes...chips and salsa were so-so.  Great atmosphere.

Excellent food and service!!! The made to order guacamole is absolutely incredible! The carnitas are some of the best I have ever had...perfectly cooked with moist inside and crispy outside. Great salsa with two varieties (mild and hot). Recommend without reservation and I will be returning (and soon).

I have been a very loyal customer of Charanda's for many years, of course starting at the Rock Hill location. I won't be returning to the Fort Mill location again. The last three times service has just been horrible. Don't get me wrong the food was good but the service is frustrating at best. Our bean and cheese dip never came until I reminded the waiter. This was after we were almost done with our meal. No drink refills. Not one until he asked me if I wanted my check. I said yes and I asked him if we could have refills on our drinks. The refills came and I was brought unsweetened tea. I was drinking sweet tea. Sorry but this location has lost a very loyal and repeat customer. If your going to go to Charanda's you might want to take the time and go to the Rock Hill location.

Four stars for lunch specials that extend from weekdays to include Saturday as well as a $2 special on Corona and Corona Light. That's a great place right there.  And the food? I'm a fan. I chose from the lunch menu, the Burrito Texicano. Americanized and with a Tex-Mex sort of vibe to it, the burrito was filled with ground beef and beans, then topped with white queso and crumbled bacon. A nice pile of rice on the side, this was a rather tasty meal and as a lunch portion, pretty good.  Chips were fresh and hot, served with a hot salsa and a more mild version. Both were good.  Good Mexican food, beer specials, I'm definitely a fan!

column23: 0Im8_WuAD_dyvg2ZI41KpQ

I'm surprised at the negative reviews of this place. We have been 3x at different times during the day and have NEVER had a bad dinning experience or bad service. The service is always prompt and accurate. The food is good and the guacamole is fresh and not even close to being runny or "from the store." Chunky and fresh just like it should be. For a small restaurant still working out the details of being relatively new, I hope the reviews will continue to improve as does the restaurant itself.

column23: Got the 8 oz filet and a NY strip last week.  Best steak I've ever had.  And great customer service.  Go try this new local business!

I am upset that I did not visit this place earlier! First point of major excitement (at least for my household) is the fact that they sell British bacon. As someone who has dated an expat for years I can attest to how difficult it is to source this item without paying exorbitant shipping costs.  The owner greeted us as we were browsing and took us through all the meats and sauces they have for sale. It is sourced locally and organically when possible and is vacuum sealed to ensure freshness for as long as possible. Other than bacon we purchased two sirloin filets which the owner gave me some great advice on how to cook. As much as I love steak cooking filet has always been a challenge for me but these two came out beautifully!  Since the filets were on a 15% off special it came to about $22 for both. A little pricy but really only a couple dollars more per steak than a grocery store and much better quality. I will definitely be back for my proteins for special occasion meals, and I am sure the boyfriend will go frequently for the bacon!

column23: Just moved to town. Went to the driving range on a crisp cool day. Had slacks on and a solid colored long sleeve shirt with no collar. Was told I couldn't hit balls without a collared shirt. Only one person on the range. Pretty stuffy for a public course in Fort Mill.
If I could give negative stars I absolutely would.  I've played or hit balls there 20 times and the personnel all have the worst attitudes and communication skills.  The course is average at best.
Love this golf course! Warm weather will only make it more beautiful. Put Fort Mill Golf Club on your list to play in 2017.

column13: Auto Parts & Supplies;Automotive;Mortgage Brokers;Home Services;Real Estate
column23: I don't work on my cars much but I do simple things like wipers and usually get my car batteries here. We bought a Duralast for our Honda Odyssey about 3 years ago and within about 18 months it died. They replaced it with a new battery and prorated most of the cost which I thought was reasonable but I was disappointed that the battery died so quickly. Flash forward 15 months and this new battery is now dead. So why the 5 star rating? After jumping the car and driving to my mechanic's shop I had the battery replaced there with an Interstate battery and took the old battery back to AutoZone, and even though it was beyond the 1 year replacement warranty they gave me a full refund with no hassle. The manager provided great customer service and turned what was a disappointing experience into a positive one. I probably won't buy another battery there but I will continue to use them for my other DIY items.

column13: Auto Parts & Supplies;Automotive;Mortgage Brokers;Home Services;Real Estate
column23: I was selling my car when the battery decided to die on me. I knew Auto Zone can test and install batteries, so I thought it would be a good option to cut time. It took at least five minutes for anyone to even come out of the back room to help up and the gentleman had a rude attitude and was rushing us the whole time. He told me the only battery that would fit my Honda Accord was the top of the line battery when I could clearly see other batteries with the same fit. I did not feel like I was getting quality service so I told him I would go someplace else for the battery and ask if he could help me get it started again. He walked to the back of the building and came back 5 mins later with the jump start equipment. After about a minute, he said that it wasn't going to work and he would have to get someone to jump start it with his or her car and then proceeded to help another customer. I had to ask someone in the parking lot to help me push the car to a parking space and jump start the car. Long story short, I will not be going back to AutoZone and the Walmart down the road was more than half the price and the service was better.

column13: Auto Parts & Supplies;Automotive;Mortgage Brokers;Home Services;Real Estate
column23: These guys are awesome! They gave me a free test on my battery to see how it was doing. They said it needed to be charged fully. A friend of mine tested my battery and said it was about dead, and I needed A new one. We took the battery back to AutoZone and they kept it overnight and found that it would not take a charge. So I guess that means a new battery for me. But I really appreciated their service because if the battery could have been charged, that would've save me the whole hassle of dealing with getting my battery replaced. They were extremely friendly and very polite, and helpful trying to match touch up paint for My car .

column23: I was with  Morningstar for a little over a year and I loved the customer service and facility! Susan is an awesome Manager and Deigo helped out anytime he could.  The unit I had was climate controlled, carts were always available, and staff always there if needed.  The cost of my unit was very reasonable compared to other companies in the area.  If I ever need to rent a unit this will be the place I return too!

Stay away from Morning Star Storage Fort Mill.  As we were moving into our new home, our movers found that our storage unit was infested with fire ants.  Thousands of ants set up in our boxes in back of unit.  We did not store any type of food in storage .  We also used Pods to store and had great experience with them without a issue.  Stick with Pods or a climate controlled storage facility.

column23: I had such a great experience with Morningstar Storage in Fort Mill.  Susan and Diego were awesome.  Diego showed me around the facility - which was beautiful.  The facility is very nice and clean.  They have so many units.  Diego showed me indoor (climate controlled) and outdoor units.  The facility has carts for people to utilize. This was the most pleasant experience I've ever had with a storage company.  They have particular locks you have to purchase... cylinder locks, but you could use them elsewhere in the future with the purchase of a certain latch... I am looking to see where you can purchase those.  Overall I had a wonderful experience, and I highly recommend this facility.  Thank you.

Unfortunately I succumbed to paying thousands of dollars with the honest belief that a professional matchmaking service could assist me in finding a compatible mate in light of my busy schedule. I was hopeful for months even after paying the sum that the service would find someone that at the very least fit the following parameters: single, male, a profession\/had a job, between the ages of 30-39, and no children. However, after 6 months of lead after lead that did not fit these parameters I lost hope. I remembered though that I bought the package that I could resale and transfer any unused portion to another buyer. The initial therapist\/salesperson had stated that the matchmaking service would assist me in reselling the unused portion. Therefore, upon my discontent that I knew there would be no refunds, I contacted the service to move forward with selling my unused portion to another person. As the therapist had pointed out, there are always those out there that are less fortunate than I. Lo and behold, upon this call, I was told that I would have to find the buyer. A buyer for a service that I would never recommend to any of my friends? Absolutely not! I was utterly frustrated because of the misrepresentations in not only the available referrals but also the exact parameters of the "resale" option. Had I known I would have to find the buyer, I would have never purchased the package. Please, please, please do not waste your time or money on this service. The deceit and disappointment are not worth it. Spend your money elsewhere. Trust me, I have had more success with Tinder than I have had with this matchmaking service.

DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY!!! THIS IS A SCAM!!! these people simply take advantage of those of us who are lonely, frustrated and discouraged from dating. DO NOT be scammed. I was vulnerable, and wanted to believe this would work. After they got my money, I was 'matched' with someone who didn't fit my criteria - lived way too far. Then months went by. I was so frustrated, I contacted a reporter to expose them and lo and behold, the same day he contacted them, I got a new 'match'. Nothing came of this, I can only encourage you to save your money. you will still be alone and out of alot of money. shame on these people

I should've listen to my intuition!  I spent money (not a great deal-but TOO much - actually any amount of money for them is too much!). I also spoke to Nancy at first. What an absolute scam!  I'm pissed at them and disappointed with myself!  I started to walk away and should have-what a hoax!  I met ONE man that wasn't even close to my "type!"  DO NOT fall into this scam!!!  They should be shut down!

Scammer Nancy convinces you that you'll be lonely and no one, including your children will take care of you and that you should join, otherwise you're going to die alone. She sends out pictures of clients to people and makes fun of them all the while trying to take their money from them. She is a soulless person who has no conscience and just wants to make this sale and then passes you on to people who will never find you a date. Steer clear unless you want to get taken for all the money that you have. She preys on old people as well. And will fleece them out of their entire retirement savings just to make a sale.

column23: STOP - DO NOT SIGN UP! I really wish I had read the reviews below before throwing these pathetic, unprofessional, scammers $8,000 dollars. I am a professional single who works from home and had recently relocated to Charlotte, where I did not know anyone. I liked that they did a background check but honestly, I would rather take my chances on Match or any other reasonable priced site. They did nothing but try to set me up with men 15 years older than me who were not even divorced. Then got mad at me when I refused. They lied about people's profiles and in nearly a year I had only two dates. One was so gross and rude, I could not believe they would even try to set me up with him. Nancy acted like they had a line of men just waiting for me and I was such a catch that I was going to be so busy. It was crickets for months. Then Theresa was as unprofessional and rude as they come. I was then told she was let go and to please give it another chance to only be set up with a guy who never called or another 65 year old. I am taking this to WRAL "5 on Your Side" - if anyone here below cares to join me, let me know. I want to alert anyone any everyone so no one else gets duped out of this kind of money. They should be shut down. Total sham.

column23: SCAM!! SCAM!! SCAM!!! Don't waste your MONEY or TIME on these people! I was a member since November 2015 and here it is Aug 2016 and they have not yet to match me with anyone in my age group or criteria. You will be better off on tinder, POF, match or any online dating sites. The sales person Brittany Williams at the location that I signed up ensured me it was men my age waiting for someone like (keep in mind I'm 30). The matchmaker called me named Teresa (who called me from some customer service hot line somewhere in the US). Teresa began setting me up with men 20yrs older than me which was not in contract. Also, I did not want any men with children because I do not have children myself. She told me it's find to hard to a man with no kids nowadays and for me to settle.  What a joke!! This should have been a big red flag. Things went downhill from my second match. She started setting me up with people that was not compatible or did not share the same interest. So after having several talks with Teresa, expressing my concerns, there was no changes. So I started to ignore her phone calls because when I asked to speak with a supervisor to express my concerns they were not available. You want to know why because the matchmakers are FAKE...you are dialing a CALL CENTER. So since I couldn't get in touch with anyone I took it upon myself to go the office at Fort Mill, SC to speak to the sales person (Brittany Williams) who signed me up. I took a day off from work and arrived at the office and not to my surprise the doors were LOCKED! The reason is because they don't like any surprises. Bottom line I was not able to speak with Brittany and the other lady Nicole told me she had a client and couldn't speak to me and make an appointment and to call client services. This was a big run around and a bunch of lies...I've been calling client services AKA call centers and no one has call me back to solve my issue. But I have NEWS for them. I have a family member who works for the news and she will get my story out there. Just wanted to share my story and experience with you all. My advice is to trust God when it comes to love and not people.

What a horrible experience!   Somehow they got my number, and continued to call me after I told them that I wasn't interested in spending money to get signed up with them, as I knew how it worked.  She wanted me to come in anyway, and when I got there, I spoke with Nancy, who seemed very interested in getting to know more about me.  At this point I didn't know if they were interested in me for a possible match with someone or what the purpose of the appointment was.  As I sat there in the office, I began to hear certain comments about becoming a client, so I decided to stop her in the conversation to make sure she was aware that I wasn't interested in joining and paying money to her service.  Nancy became very angry, and began speaking to me in a very disrespectful tone, and accused me of coming there and waisting her time.  She asked me why I came if I new that I wasn't going to join, and  I told her that I had already told the other lady who had called me several times that I was not interested in paying a joining fee, and she insisted that I come anyway.  Nancy told me that there is no matchmaking service where the female doesn't pay, and I corrected her as I know several which do not charge the female to join the service.  She then became irate with me and told me that I was "out of my mind", and was just extremely rude and disrespectful with her words toward me with insinuating that I was looking for someone to "take care of me"..  I chose not to get into a shouting match with her and just left her office.    I  wanted to warn people about this service, and let you know my experience.  I truly feel that this organization is a scam, and I wouldn't dare give them a penny of my money.  I've never felt so violated and disrespected because I didn't want to give her thousands of dollars to join.

Wish you could give no stars  10 month old $200+ tires with less than 10k miles and they are totally shot.   I could understand if it was over a year and over the mileage, but telling me that I have to buy new tires out of my pocket, have the distributor they partnered with and who has confirmed the issue send the tires back, and then they will look at them and see if I should get replacements. This process takes 3 months!  Why would I buy another set of tires from a company that won't back the first?? Had they said there must have been a defect since they should last longer than 10k miles, I could see giving them another try. But all they do is keep sending you the warranty info that you already have and never respond to the actual issue.   This one is easy - just stay away from this company.

column23: I was recently told by my BMW dealer that I needed to replace my rear tires. I was totally surprised because I only have 16,000 miles on my car. I confronted the dealer about this and he referred me to the Continental manufacturer. when I called the customer service line they told me to bring my car to a local continental dealer and have them measure my tires and send them the results from there they were going to let me know if there was going to be any pro-ration on the tires. To my disappointment they informed me that there was nothing they could do for me. I will never again buy continental tires for any of my vehicles, they do not back their product and the tread wear warranty is a farce, they will look for any excuse not to pay for their inferior tires.

column23: Bad tire and a company that does not back all of their products.  In the 15 months and 15,300 miles that I have owned my Continental CONTISPORTCONTACT 5's I have had little positives to take.  I have never had a tire so prone to punctures and leak.  I also have never once had a summer tire need replacement after 15 months and 15,300 miles, especially considering how much I baby my Audi S3.  Just to be safe Audi checked my alignment and my car was good so neither my driving nor a bad alignment was causing premature wear.  The Audi S3 was also purchased brand new from Audi, not used.  When calling Continental Customer Care support line I realized how useless they are.  While they were not rude it was almost like talking to a brick wall as I felt like the person was tuning me out after a while and waiting for me to hang up.  There was no sympathy, no understanding for my issues, no compensation for such horrible tread life.  I was just told it is a performance tire (aka summer tire) so they don't offer any tread life warranty\/compensation.  Funny because Michelin, for example, makes a set of super sports for my car that is also a performance tire with a 3 year 30K warranty and it is not unheard of for a tire company to back their summer tires, especially for poor life and numerous leaking issues.  End of the day my experience with Michelin Super Sport summer tires and Pirelli P Zero summer tires is much more positive.  They both have better life and less issues while receiving more aggressive driving compared to my S3 (S3 is my daily driver) all while driving on the same roads that my S3 drives on.  Simply put there are better tires than Continental out there for every category.  I will never own another set of Continental tires nor will I ever recommend them, unless of course they come on a future car I buy brand new like they did on my S3.
Great people, Quality work, Great price. These guys and Jennifer Rock!  Don't let their hours of operation put you off they have a solution for every situation. Just call them

Tori, Richard, Mike, and Pumpkin all did a great job servicing my vehicle and giving me a fair price for great work. It is nice to find somebody with integrity that you can trust these days! If I could recommend them more highly I would.

My car's A\/C died and I needed to get it fixed fast.  Mike, a former B-52 crew chief, got my car blowing cold air fast at a very good price.  I have nothing but good to say about this shop and the people who work it.  Be sure to thank Mike for his service and mention your own.  BZ!

column23: I have had to take our son there twice in 4 weeks (strep and the flu! ). The office staff is so kind. They are attentive and we haven't had to wait more than 10 minutes once we check in. The nurses are so gentle and caring to the patients and parents. Top notch service, even when you fee so terrible.
Not really urgent care. We were only clients in the waiting room when we arrived and we waited over an hour to be seen. Doctor and nurse were nice.

column23: I had to bring my daughter to urgent care today due to upper respiratory infection. I was greeted by the secretary. When I proceeded to give her my TWO insurance cards she advised me that they didn't take my primary insurance ( which I understood) but they did take the secondary insurance. I advised her that they needed to bill out the primary insurance to get the denial for the secondary insurance to pay. She became extremely rude with me and would not take either insurance at that point and told me that if I wanted my daughter to be seen I would have to private pay. I became very upset and asked her why I would have to private pay when they in fact took the secondary insurance. I asked to speak with someone in billing and she advised me that (PIEDMONT EXPRESS CARE AT SUTTON ROAD) does not have a billing department. I then asked to speak with someone higher than her. About 5 minutes goes by and then the nurse comes out and she advised me that she would not be able to be seen due to me stating that the secondary would not have been covered if they only billed that alone, because I have a primary that they didnt accept. I then asked to speak to someone in charge. They both left the front area, and agin didnt come back for about 5 mins and then the nurse came back stated the doctor was busy seeing patients (even though there were no patients in the waiting room) . I feel I am being discriminated against due to my insurance, who is based out of NY (CDPHP-Capitol District Physicians Health Plan) and the other is BCBS, both of which have full coverage! These two girls were completely rude and disrespectful that its no wonder the community is fighting to keep Piedmont out. They will not have my support and I then went to a different Urgent Care today and was treated much differently.
Always fast and attentive!  Was seen there today and I never have to wait long even just walking in without calling ahead. Dr. Jenny is the best!

My second time here. The first time was great. In and out in no time and they were not busy. This second time I went to their website and scheduled an appointment. I arrived and explained I had an appointment.  So far I've been sitting here for 45 minutes. There were only 2 people waiting when I walked in. They both went back some time ago. Feels like scheduling the appointment was a waste of time.

These guys are awesome! Pleasant, friendly and professional customer service! I was able to be seen earlier than my scheduled time, which, as you know, never happens when it comes to urgent care. In and out in no time, yet still thorough. You can tell the entire staff truly cares about their work. I don't like complaining or giving negative reviews and fortunately, I don't have to with this business. Thank you!

column23: When our AC wasn't working at the end of last summer, I noticed the coil was leaking Freon.  Lee's came out, gave me an estimate for replacing it and pumped enough Freon into the system to get us through the summer.  I thought the price for replacing the coil was a little high, so I called other places.  All of them were asking about the unit and none of them had seen it.  I knew it was ok and Lee's confirmed that.  I called Lee's back and they came out and replaced the coil.  There was also a bad capacitor on the unit that they replaced without charge.  They are nice people.  The prices are a little high, but they are local and they will not sell you anything you don't need.

column23: I would never recommend this company!  Purchased an annual maintenance plan for heating and cooling system, and my fault for pre-paying, but they would never return my call when I called to schedule spring and fall maintenance visits.  Took my money and never did the work.

I was pleased with the service, but their answering service is pretty terrible, and it was difficult to get a call back, even when I reached a tech directly--that's where they lost a star.  We have a slow leak that requires a recharge every few years or so, and it took us a while to realize that the bigger firms in the area have a lot more salespeople than service techs.  At least 3 other technicians and a supervisor from big firms told us that our compressor was shot, the core was bad, and we would need a new unit on our less than 10 year old home.  A friend who works in the business confided that service techs for the big firms earn an embarrassingly low hourly wage, and don't love going in attics to troubleshoot small problems.  On the flip side, if they can convince you to get a new unit, they pocket a several hundred dollar commission, and they won't have to set foot in your attic, since that falls to the "install crew."  Needless to say, we were glad to finally get a Lee's tech out to our house, since there were no games--just ice cold air.  We would definitely use Lee's again.

Call from tenant in my home that heat was not working.  Called Lee's and received initial call back right away.  Got my system working again only for it to quit working the next day.  House is 6 yrs old.  Called back to get them to come back out and figure out what needed to be fixed.  Never got a call back.

called Lees on a Thurs for service , they kept putting me off , promised me a service call on saturday.  I waited all day, finally at 4:30 pm i called and the tech told me he had just woken up and that he had pneumonia but he would come on over.   i told him dont bother, i will use another company from now on.   with a high of 40 tomorrow and a wasted saturday waiting for them i could never recommend this company to anyone

This is by far the worst motel 6 I've ever stayed in. If you are looking for an authentic Turkish prison experience then this is the place for you. The rooms smell awful and have not been updated since they installed those TV's from what appears to be 1997. There is not even mesh on the windows so if you dare open them to alleviate the horrible stench of rotting hotel you will flood your room with mosquitoes.

column23: If you're planning to visit Carowinds and need a cheap hotel that is close to the park, this is the place you want to be.  Even for a holiday weekend, the rate was $54 a night (standard weekend rate) via making the reservation online.  The hotel itself sits behind a Texaco gas station and is near a Shoney's so there is easy access to food and gas for your trip.  You make a left at the stoplight for the highway and drive about 500 feet to the next stoplight to turn into the Carowinds entrance, it's that close.  The front desk staff was friendly and helpful and made sure I was all set up.  I had requested a non-smoking room and I was put in one, no problems there.  The room I took (1 king size bed) is your basic hotel room with a bed, bathroom, wardrobe, and cable TV.  Everything was very clean and looked well maintained.  Wi-Fi is available for $3 a day, you go down to the front desk to buy an access code from them.  There is a pool and laundry facilities are available on-site.  I had no problems with noise or anything else from guests.  The only snag I ran into was trying to order a pizza delivery.  The business had just started leaving menus at the hotel and it turns out that the hotel address used to be Carowinds Blvd, but has recently changed to something else.  The new address is reflected on the business card at the front desk so just use that to help you out in case the business has an issue with your address.  However, I get the feeling that if a place has been delivering to this hotel for a while, they know where it's at if you tell them you're at the one near Carowinds.  This will be the first hotel I look at the next time I visit Carowinds, or if I am out in the Charlotte area for other reasons.

column23: I'd easily give this 5 stars if not for two things. One, you pay for wifi. Two, the room was about $60, but they pulled out around $100. It was the friends card I was staying with and he checked in and out. So I'm not sure if it was for possible damages, then they reimbursed you or what.   I WAS however very impressed with what I got for the money. The place was extremely clean. Looked like it had been remodeled recently. Very fresh meat look in the rooms. Great huge shower with a seat. From top to bottom and all corners, place looked great. Nice hardwood floors in room. Tv worked good and was easy to use.   I'll stay here again easily if I can figure out why they pull more than the room out of your card. I can deal with no free wifi. They do offer some from $3-5 a day depending on what you need.

column23: I would have almost rather slept in my car. There were crickets in the bathroom in the night and my husband saw roaches in the room in the morning. The furniture was old and dated. Sheets were scratchy. AC didn't work at first, front desk instructed us to unplug it for 15 minutes, plug it back in, wait awhile, and then try it. The only plus is that they allow pets which was great for our long distance move. Toilet flushes with such power it splashes all over your legs if you don't move quickly. Never again. It's very cheap to stay here, but I've paid maybe $20 more for many much nicer hotels.

column23: From the moment I walked into my room I knew it wasn't going to be a pleasant stay! The first thing I noticed when walking into the room was 2 pieces of chewed up gum on the headboard of the bed. It was fresh almost like the last person that walked in the room left it. I took some tissue and cleaned it up. Secondly, there were Ants everywhere! I was so afraid Ants would get into my luggage so every night before I went to bed I'd make sure my luggage was all zipped up and I'd store it in my car during the 2 days I was in town. On our final day leaving, we saw roaches crawling on the wall of the hallway outside our room. Housekeeping didn't clean my room and when I went to tell the person at the front desk, they saw that housekeeping had noted in the system that they left us with clean towels and clean trash cans...BUT THEY REALLY HADN'T! We stayed on the first floor (Room 104) and the neighbors were extremely noisy. The room  was very small and was not worth the amount we paid. Plus, no free Wifi! Like seriously!?! It's 2016!!! Probably the best part about the entire room and my stay, was walking out of it heading home!

I was satisfied with my stay at this hotel.  My room was functional and clean. The staff were friendly and accommodating. Likewise, the rates were competitive. I had no problems with my stay, and would probably stay there again.  My thanks goes out to this hotel's owners and operators. I am grateful for your service.

My friend & I stayed here back in June 2016 during the middle of the month. We stayed here for one night since we spent the day next door at Carowinds.   The location was perfect, clean motel, no issues, comfortable beds, large bathroom, room was cold, smelt clean, and was large enough for us two to walk around. The staff at the front desk was nice and friendly. There are some eatery places within walking distances here. The motel is right off the hwy.   If you want to, you could walk to Carowinds from here. I spent like a rock in my bed for the night. My friend liked the room as well. We had a with 2 beds and still had room to walk about.   I highly recommend staying here for a safe, clean, guaranteed motel stay. Excellent spot for visiting Carowinds next door. I approve.

column23: We had them move a very expensive bedroom suit and when they were done we left right behind them to go clean up the old house. The next day we go to put the bed together and notice that the headboard had been broke. So we call and tell them they tell us they have to talk to the movers. They talk to them don't know what was said they find pieces of my headboard in the truck. So the tell me they have to look into what to do about it and they will get back with me. The next day we get a email saying that they are going to cut me a check for 60 dollars for the headboard that cost me 1100 dollars 2 years ago. Needless to say I wouldn't recommend nor will I ever use these people again. Thinking of getting bill McGinty on the news to show how they treat your stuff then when they mess it up they don't do nothing to fix or replace it

Had such an amazing experience with this company from start to finish that I will be using them from this point forward. The movers were professional and courteous, management was more than accommodating, and the team made what is usually a hectic and stressful experience, one that was worry free. Above and beyond my expectations, would highly recommend and have already booked them again!

We recently hired B&B to move us and had the worst experience.  On the day of our move they never showed up!  Talk about stressed out!  They were unprofessional in  the way they handled it and I would not recommend them.  The guys that actually came the next day were nice but that's not the issue...the operations manager or whoever we spoke with in the office did not get back to us and still charged us for things we didn't even use like blankets and boxes.  I was not pleased and would not recommend them,.

At first, I thought I has found one of the best moving companies. They came in and looked at everything, got back to us the next day with a reasonable quote, and before packing up we had another walk through to see what all was going and to check items for previous damage. Then, it came time to pack up. The guys that came in to pack we're nice, but their packing was horrible. They left the first day around 1:30 with so much left to pack that I was worries how they were going to get it all done. The next day they said they will get it all done. The time went by and one room had not even been touched. One of the guys came in and asked if they were responsible to get everything in there and I said yes. He was upset about that so I told him not to worry about it I'll get it. They finished packing everything up and told us they were going to head out. My husband asked him if they got everything in the garage and he said yes sir.   We met them at our destination in Asheville and unloading went fairly well. However, when it came time to unpack, the hurrying they did on Saturday to finish packing us, they just through everything in boxes not caring how they packed! As we continued to unpack, we noticed things missing and thought we would find them in another box, but we didn't. The following week came and I had to head back to Charlotte for work and final cleaning of our apartment. When I got there ALL of our pictures were still there, all of the stuff was left in the garage that my husband asked about,I started opening drawers and my pot lids were all left, cake and pie pans all left, grilling stuff all left and much more. It was awful how much stuff was left!! I had to make one trip back to Asheville with my truck to the ceiling with stuff and then come back the next day!!  What is even more horrible, we fed these guys breakfast and lunch, had a fridge stocked with drinks of all sorts and tipped them at the end (which they probably didn't want the food and drinks just more money) emailed the COO and nothing! Well, he said he'd was sorry, he'd look into it and get back to me ASAP. Two weeks later and we still have not heard from him. We should have listen to our friends who were about to use them, but changed their minds because of a few things they heard. Learned our lesson!!

We used Ballantyne and Beyond to move this week. We were beyond impressed with the team of 5 who showed up! They were knowledgeable, friendly, expeditious, and hard working. Chris "Fat Boy", Scott, Antonio, Papi and Arnold were the best! They came right within a few dollars of their estimate and we'd definitely use them again.

column23: Very positive experience!! Both of the gentlemen that helped me move were courteous, professional and very careful with all my items. I would recommend to anyone looking for a local mover. They got the job done and did it amazingly well.

I was extremely satisfied with my interaction with this company.   They gave me an accurate estimate with no surprises at the end.   They showed up on time with the expected number of men who were respectful and friendly.   No damages occurred during my move.  The only negative was that they had no empty boxes on the truck.  I was expecting wardrobe boxes to be delivered upon their arrival and there were none.  Otherwise,  my experience with B & B was very good.  I would use them again.

I wanted everyone to know the  horrid experience we experienced, using this company.  We moved while living in Charlotte, locally, once and they were great.   When getting quotes to move to Colorado, we asked them if they would move cross country, since we had such a great experience in town.   They gave us a quote for one truck and told us they happened to be moving another couple to Colorado at the same time and would combine our things on the truck.   We were staying in an apt temporarily for 3 months until we closed on our house. So less than 1\/4 of our things were being moved into the apt...prelabled by us ....and the remainder was going to storage.    When asked about payment prior to moving, they stated we could pay with a personal check, that was fine.   When they arrived at storage, they told us they needed a cashiers check.   They would not unload our things until they had one.  This was at 6 pm on a Saturday evening.  We had to pay for the time they stayed in town until Monday morning when we could get a check to do so.  Then, they unloaded the last of our stuff at the apartment after unloading the majority in storage.   The guy left to go to his truck to get the paperwork for us to sign...never came back.....and screeched off down the road!  We immediately called the owner of Ballantyne and Beyond as I had already started to open some wardrobe boxes.  The boxes did not have our hanging clothes in them.   The bar had been removed and they were filled to the brim....with what we later realized were the contents of several other smaller boxes DUMPED out into the wardrobe box.  It seems that they quoted us one truck which ended up not being enough.  So they took every one of our smaller boxes and dropped all our hanging clothes into the bottom of every wardrobe and dumped the contents of as many boxes as possible in to the boxes until they were filled.    They did this with at least half of our boxes- we have a family of FIVE.   They stole all of my husbands power tools.  We found garage items with legos dumped in.   Shoes, with kitchen utensils dumped on top.  American girls buried under all of our wedding keepsakes.   All of my children's special boxes I had with all of their firsts, baptism certificates, locks of hair.  coming home outfits, first pacifier, etc, cards from family.....have never been found.  The boxes are there.  The contents were empty.  NOTHING was as labeled.  Our brand new front load washer had a HUGE dent in the front, our new fridge had a horizontal scrape across the front.  Almost every box had broken items in it.    The owner, Everett, denied everything.  They are thieves and dishonest people in general.  Interesting to hear the experience Anna, below, posted.  These people are thieves and criminals.  Do not use them.  Tell everyone you know.  Our experience was in December of 2011.  They are still continuing to take advantage of people, I see.

column23: We recently completed a move using B&B movers. Our team of Chris, Brian and Reco were awesome. They came at the discussed time each day, worked extremely hard, asked before taking breaks and were professional and nice.  These guys made our move as pleasant as a move can be.  I would definitely recommend them for your next move.

This was my first time hiring movers. The movers were polite and respectful but smelled of weed when they walked in. When we got to our destination, one of the movers stated they left a piece od furniture needed to put my dresser and mirror together. He said he will leave the screws with me so I can do it myself. He only left 3 screws...I need 6. I was not happy about this but I just let it go. They rushed out of my apartment and asked for a tip several times. I went into my bedroom to find a large hump in my mattress. The springs on my mattress shifted as if the movers put something hard on\/against it or they folded it. I called the company and spoke with the owner, Greg Causey, who informed me of the claims process. The company offered me $84 for a king sized mattress... $84!!! I would caution anyone who uses this company. I paid $712 for their services for them to offer me $84. I will never use them again.

We moved from Charlotte to Indian Land over the course of several months.   We moved most of the smaller and fragile items ourselves but wanted professionals to deal with the large, heavy items.   We got a number of quote and these guys were by far the best price, which I will admit worried me a but.  However, the 3 man crew showed up on time, efficiently loaded all the items and even helped my husband move a treadmill that we were selling across the house for easier movement later.  At the destination, they carefully moved all furniture into place and moved an existing washer dryer from the 2nd story to the basement.    We could not have been happier with their service.  They were only about 15 minutes over their estimated time but that was mostly due to the extra help with the treadmill.  We would definitely use them again for furniture moves!

Let's face it - moving is excruciating whether it's across town or across the country, but our crew from Ballantyne & Beyond made a long day of loading and unloading as much fun as could possibly be had. These guys were hard working, careful, polite, funny and engaging - if I had to hand pick a moving crew to spend 9 hours with among boxes, upended furniture and a houseful of "stuff," these would be my guys. Our move was by far the best one ever, and I appreciate Ballantyne & Beyond for helping us get settled in our new home. Thanks to Josh, Jimmy, Devonte, Lance, Hassan and John for taking such good care of our belongings and taking the stress out of the day. Thanks to Dustin, too, for coming out and giving us an accurate estimate and ensuring there were no surprises on moving day!!

column23: I had a very large move without a lot of notice. These guys were true professionals and gave me first class service.  They came in and packed, loaded and delivered all of my belongings with ease. The price was not the cheapest, but these guys don't try to be. The actual cost was lower than what was estimated.  I'd highly recommend.

Second time I've used Ballantyne and Beyond the last couple years and once again I'm beyond happy.  Professional, on time, friendly, detailed, great job by everyone involved.  They noticed I didn't pack a couple boxes very well and pointed it out to me.  I will definitely use them again.

Yet again, another great move using Ballantyne and Beyond movers. I can tell you for all of my moves, it was the same amount of time and the exact same bill. These movers hustle and are super friendly. Offer a soda, water or Gatorade and they'll be very appreciative and don't forget to tip the movers for a job well done. Thanks Ballantyne and Beyond!!!

column23: They actually made our move pleasant!   A rare thing when moving is so miserable!  The workers were on time, kind and extremely hard working.   I have referred this company to many and they have had the same positive experience.

Although I definitely like meat, this is fast becoming one of my favorite places! If you want high quality, well prepared food and you're up for a tasty dose of veggies, this is the place for you! I have know the owners casually for a number of years. They have been at this location for a while, starting out with a coffee shop, and recently reinventing themselves as a vegetarian restaurant and smoothie bar, and I am so glad they branched out because they know what they are doing! The place is very cheerful and clean looking, and the inside feels spacious even though it's a small place. In fact, you can miss it real easily because it is so small on the outside. It is part of a strip mall at the entrance of Regent Park on the opposite side of the parkway from Food Lion. The first time I had lunch they had a Dried Tomato and Scallion Quiche for their special. It was divine: very thick, about 3", in a flaky crust with a wonderful Spring Mix side salad with homemade dressing. Another time I had a Lemon Raspberry Tart. It was delicious and the texture was like butter, while the fruit flavors were intense. Most recently I had the Spanish Tamales with melted cheese and Black Bean  Pure. I loved every bite! The portions are not large, but adequate, so a big hungry guy might want more, but it is perfect for me. It's an unexpected gem of a restaurant for those who want healthy.

column23: Good, real food at fair prices.  Friendly service.  Homemade scones are fantastic. Fresh smoothies and juices made with all natural, delicious ingredients.  Just the kind of place Fort Mill needs more of.

Liked the shop at first. Made lots of purchases. Then... Purchased a Joytech Cudiod that stopped working after 2 months. Return it to the shop and was told they would take care of the problem. After not receiving any updates after 6 weeks I returned to the shop. At first they couldn't find the device then was told it was my problem. I will not be returning.

These guys only have the TOP OF THE LINE liquids in stock. Trust me, I've gone to my fare share of vape shops....the worst I've had is actually right near my house, and I WILL NOT go there anymore....this is not a large store my any means, but they get the job done, and they do it good with great prices on OUTSTANDING liquids. GO!

column23: I've been to a couple of chiropractors in the Ft Mill area and by far I like Dr. Williams the best. He listens, takes good notes and changes the therapy if something does not have the desired result the first time. I like manual adjustments so Doc Williams is for me.. I've been going here for over a year and alwayse get relief after my visit. Oh yeah let me also mention I can normally get in very quickly and virtually NO WAIT which is very important to me.

Dr Williams is the best! The thing I like about him the most, is the fact that he really listens to you. I feel I am heard, whereas a lot of doctors form opinions without really listening to what you are saying. I appreciate that he tells you each step of the way what he is doing and that his manner is so patient. Also I appreciate that he takes the whole person into consideration instead of just focusing on the injured area. I have had more success with him than anyone I have gone to. He did not require an X-Ray in order to treat me, but did a physical exam and observed my movements to assess what was needed. I feel I have made more progress with him than any of my other physical therapist or upper cervical doctors.

column23: I went here for lunch with my hubby, and we loved it! Large but comfortable, great waitress, and my Rib Eye sandwich, amazing! Awesome onion rings, great beers on tap. Go!

I live less than a mile from this establishment and have frequented the previous businesses as we can walk there.  I am a long timer in the restaurant industry and know that every one has bad days.  I always give a place a second or third try. Unfortunately once was enough for me and Ziggy's.  long story short I ordered a strip steak MR. I explained to my waiter that I will not eat a steak that is cooked to medium or over and if the kitchen was to make an error to please err on the side of rare.  The steak came to me cooked to MWell. I asked the waiter to please ask the kitchen to give it another shot for medium rare.  Once again the steak came out significantly overlooked. The waiter realized that there was a problem as my husband was almost done with his so so food and I had yet to start and asked his manager to stop by our table. The mgr asked if I would like to order something else (at this point my husband was finished) I declined.   Knowing that this wasn't the waiters fault we left our normal 20% tip and continued out the door. I am sure that everyone has experienced this situation - what was different this time was the manager follows us out the door yelling at us!!!  WHAT?  Your kitchen could not cook a steak and I'm leaving hungry and you are yelling at me?  Enough said!   We are looking forward to the next incarnation when Ziggy's closes.

In the warm weather, this place rocks.  Like literally, it's loud.  But if you're there for a good time with ggreat people, their patio is the BOMB.  I like the food, don't love it, but it does the trick after a beer or 4.
Food is tasty. Service at the bar is consistently inconsistent.  Bartenders are very nice but poorly trained. The last 3 times we have been there for taco Tuesdays,  orders have been wrong.

Was so excited when I heard tega cay was getting a sabor. I used to go to the uptown location all the time when I worked uptown. This place is amazing and if you are on a health kick you are in luck my friend. Quinoa Avocado bowl is amazing, add some shrimp and you have just upped the game. Not on a diet, good lord please do yourself a favor and get the nachos or empanadas! Carne Asada fries also take this game to another level. Right now they just have beer and wine! (Tons of local craft beers)  They have applied for the liquor license and we will soon be having margaritas with our food. Lastly, don't forget to stop by the salsa bar before you eat and grab some salsas to add flavor! Pineapple habanero salsa is the shiznick!  That's all for now! No go get you some good good! You won't be sorry!
