column23: Great restaurant in the area.  Servers\/staff are good people and the food is not truly authentic but its pretty good.  Nice environment as well for a good meal.  I recommend this place to anyone!

Delicious. The Margarita are hand shaken and the best I have had. I always ask for extra spicy garlic shrimp. The shrimp are fresh and plump and the vegetables are crisp. The service is friendly and paced well.

Science class for the clinically insane.  I'll start by saying the food was ok. Not spectacular, not terrible. That's why id give it 2 stars. However, I do not recommend coming here if you have any food allergies or dietary restrictions. Or if you don't like to be treated disrespectfully by an arrogant and overly incompetent manager.  After ordering vegetable dumplings and double checking with the host to make sure it was a vegetarian menu item, I gobbled up 1 and bit into another before realizing that I was eating meat, presumably pork. I was not happy because those few bites could make me sick, but understanding that mistakes happen, I just showed the waitress and asked for the vegetable version. The waitress Catherine was very nice and apologetic, however after a quick trip to the kitchen she returned, embarrassed, with the manager.  Apparently the meat in the dumpling had caused an argument in the kitchen and the manager, looking none too pleased after being pulled away from his cigarette, said he would fix it and came back from the kitchen with one dumpling on a small plate. He then proceeded to demonstrate what I will call "science class for the clinically insane". As he vigorously cut through the dumpling I realized that this was not a courtesy, this was a challenge.  He pulled the two halves of dumpling apart in front of me as if to show me that I was crazy, and obviously annoying him for no reason, but unfortunately the pork tumbled out of the dumpling, disproving his hypothesis.  In a twist no one saw coming, he pointed to the meat and said "see, only vegetables". I pointed to one especially greasy lump of meat and asked "what type of vegetable is this?" To which he replied " I don't know...vegetables. You know, tofu or something."  If you are ok with eating things without knowing what is in them, this place might be fine. If, like most humans, you prefer to know what your are spending your money on and putting into your body, my advice is to avoid this place.  And if you are from Red Bowl and would like to know which manager it was that was so rude, I can't tell you because he never introduced himself and wasn't wearing a name tag. I can tell you that this unfortunate lunch took place on 4-2-15 at 1:30pm.

Best high quality Asian style food around Indian land forsure. Service is pretty good but food taste great. Its a little pricy so I mostly go for special events and such. Definitely recommended if looking for legit sushi too.
Great food an very intentive service!  We were never disappointed!  Congrats and keep up what you're doing!

WORST. THAI. FOOD. EVER. I don't even know how they can call it Thai Food. There wasn't any curry in the red curry. The Tom Kai soup was totally inedible. The only edible food was the Crab Wontons and the fortune cookies.

Love the potstickers! A hit every time.  Recommend.

column23: Food was very good and our server was friendly, but a tad harried (hence the 4 stars, instead of 5).   I had a Bento Box and my husband had a Stir Fry Bowl. We both really enjoyed our meals.   Our server was very nice, but she must have been new. She didn't know the answers to a couple of basic questions, she didn't know the menu, and she seemed frazzled. We noticed that the manager picked up on it, too and he pulled her aside a couple of times to talk to her. For example, the Stir Fry Bowl came with a choice of different rices and "Chinese Noodles". We asked what kind of noodles they are and her response was "I don't know"...not "Let me find out". She actually said, I don't know. UGH!  We had to ask her to find out for us.  BTW...they are Lo Mein noodles. :-)   I understand that there's a learning curve and I most certainly can look past the newbie jitters, but it drives me batty when servers don't know the menu or offer to have someone else answer questions that they can't answer.  With all of that being said....we still really liked it there. Very clean, very good food, and decent prices.

column23: Delicious fusion Asian food! We were served by James and he made our family dining experience very enjoyable!!

5 adults 2 teenages for dinner on 3\/25\/2016.  All placed orders, normal wait for food and 6 of 7 dinners come out.  Waiter came back to table to apologize as last order was not prepared with the others.  Told waiter to tell manager to take 7th dinner off the bill and to pack the food to go.  Found out at home(took 2 cars) that manager came over to ask how meal was and he was told about the problem.  As the waiter brings over the 7th meal the manager says, your food is here now.  He should have been kissing our a** with apologies and he says that.  Johnny Red Bowl change your name to Fredo.  You are dead to me.

Giving three stars comparing it to the other one off Providence road. Sushi is good and equal to the other one however the other dishes are no match to the one on Providence.  Wait staff is good and takes care of your needs.  The manager walks around looking at everyone however doesn't do anything which can be a bit annoying especially if no one is in the restaurant.  Overall an OK spot to stop in an eat in a pinch but if you can make the drive to Providence road go for it.

We were long time customers, mostly due to the fact that this is the only place in town.  But the last two times that we were here, the service was awful when they messed up our order twice. Won't be back.

Free wifi. Very clean. Nicely updated. Excellent AAA rate on a Sunday night. I would definitely stay here again.  The bathroom was odd. The refurb kept the original tub and fixtures, but the fixtures were loose and wobbled when you turned on the shower. This should have been addressed while the new shower surround was going in.   The piece of furniture that holds the TV, microwave, and fridge is way too large and is placed so that the space between the end of the bed and the front of this bureau\/entertainment center is a very narrow aisle and it makes the room feel very cramped.  Check-in began at 1500 and it was well after 1600 when we arrived, but the front desk had to radio housekeeping to see if they had a room ready. If a very busy, sold-out hotel has to turn over to another very busy, sold-out night, there can definitely be a lot of calls to housekeeping when you're checking people into rooms as quickly as they are cleaned, but this was not that. It was a relatively quiet Sunday. It makes me wonder how they would manage when they are actually busy.

column23: Booked to stay for 3 nights, got to our room and it was filthy. There was food crumbs on the floor and the baseboards had dead bugs and food stuck to them. Then we noticed crayon markings all over the walls along with a hole in the wall that needed to be patched. Next we found hairs on the bathroom floor. I went and complained about the room and they gave us a different room which was better but still subpar. The second room's comforter had a big brown yellowish stain, hairs again on the bathroom floor, and bugs in the tub. Obviously cleanliness is not a priority for this hotel. Seek one of the cleaner hotels located near it instead.

This is on the short list of my least favorite hotels. The website is VERY deceptive.  There is only a weird Mexican restaurant attached with limited hours. The room and hallway had a very strange and unappealing smell. The whole hotel desperately needs updating. The pool was out of order in mid July.  It is by no means an expensive hotel, but the price seems high for what you get. There are newer smaller hotels in the area that I would go with instead.

column23: Absolutely HORRIBLE experience.  Didn't even end up staying here. We booked this hotel for our 15 wedding anniversary.  We booked a package deal that gave us 2 tickets to Carowinds.  We had made dinner reservations to a nice restaurant in Charlotte so we made sure to arrive at the hotel with enough time to shower and get ready for dinner.  (We arrived around 6 p.m.)  When we walked in we were informed that their internet company had the internet down and they didn't know when it would be back up. Because of this we were told that they could not check in any reservations and they didn't know when they would be able to. The two girls at the front desk were extremely unhelpful and kept insisting that they could not do anything without the internet. We informed them that we had a package deal and one of the girls even said "Oh you guys are the ones with the Carowinds tickets?" They still refused to do anything to help. I asked for the customer number at the corporate office so I could talk to someone there.  The girl there said she couldn't find it and also said that corporate wouldn't be able to do anything as well. There were several people that while we were there were told the same thing.  In the lobby, there was a family sitting there with the same problem of trying to find a place to stay. We were told we could cancel our reservation and go to another hotel.    I asked if they had any backup plan in case the internet was ever to go out.  They said they didn't.and they didn't know how to do anything without the internet. I asked about a manager there, I was told the manager couldn't help, when I asked about an Area Manager or District Manager we were told that that person was out of town and couldn't help. All they kept telling us is that it's not their fault.  While we understand that the internet being down was not their fault we find it absolutely ridiculous that they would not have measures put in place that they would still be able to check in their customers if their internet was down. It was poor customer service not to have a back up plan to be able to take care of their customers.   I looked up the guest relations phone number on my phone and spoke with a representative there.  He said they should be able to check us in without having the internet.  He even put me on hold and contacted the hotel himself and was told the same thing.  He said that they should try to get us into another comparable hotel if they are unable to get us checked in.  The girl at the desk said they wouldn't do that.  They gave us a list of hotels around the area (that were not comparable).  So we left because by this time we needed to find a place at least to change for our dinner reservation and make our dinner reservation on time.  When we were almost finished with our dinner, we called the hotel to check on the status..they said they were still unable to check us in.  After dinner, we even  called another Clarion and were told by that Clarion that there was a way they should be able to check us in without the internet.  They said they would call the hotel to tell them how to do it...after 20 minutes, we called back to the hotel where we had the reservations and were told they still were not able to check us in.  Finally at 10:15 p.m. we had enough. We found a competitor's hotel and they gave us a great deal. (Kudos to Fairfield Inn!!)  This was an absolutely nightmare of a situation!!!

Can I give zero stars? Guess not. Stay away. Not a good value unless you get what you expect from a nationally known brand. Dirty towels. DIRTY TOWELS found instead of clean. How can you trust them?! And zero customer service. Good luck if you try them.

column23: I came to Infinite Wellness suffering from back and sciatic pain, along with frequent migraines and intense random body aches and pains from fibromyalgia. Both Dr. Curtis and Dr. Johnson were very proactive in relieving my various pains, as well as gentle so as not to create more pain. My husband and 2 children are also under care, and our health has improved.   Recently I have been able to become a part of a trial for a new fibromyalgia treatment, and I have more energy and less pain than I have had in the past 25 years. I highly recommend Infinite Wellness to anyone looking for a caring chiropractic practice.

column23: I have been a patient for a little over a 1 year and I have never felt better!  The service and the treatments are amazing.  I have tried a few chiropractic treatments after a serious car accident in 2000 and none of them relieved the pain in my neck and shoulders like Infinite Wellness has.    When I first visited the office I was skeptical of their method, but it has helped me feel 100% better.  The best part is, they put me on a treatment plan that didn't last forever!  For a long time I only had to go once a month and now every few months.  That's a relief because some of the past treatments required so much time and money out of my pocket.    Now I can workout and do yard work without feeling pain.  Which is how I should feel since I'm only 32!  If you are in pain, you need to visit Infinite Wellness Center and tell everyone you know to go too!

The salon has great stylists who are accommodating, friendly and listen to the wants and needs of their clients. The shop is new, clean and well maintained. It's worth the trip for my husband and I. Donna is our favorite but it's worth giving any of the girls a try! Everybody leaves looking fabulous.
Donna is amazing!  If you are looking for the best in cut color and highlights...dont settle for less than the best at Southern Roots!!

column23: My awesome hairstylist Donna Williams along with 2 other great stylists have opened this new salon, which is warm and welcoming. Donna has made me look amazing for years. She's the best, hands down!!

I have been going to Tiffany for years, and she does a great job every time! I have gotten my hair cut and colored with her, and I always love the results. Prices are very reasonable too. Highly recommend!

I am so happy I found this salon. I have ALOT of hair!!! It is very dry and unmanageable. My hair was really long and dead looking. I found this place on yelp and decided to give it a try. Got my hair cut and dried with Tracy. She was amazing!! Not only did my hair come out looking great but she did it all in just a little over an hour (which with my super think hair is much faster than anyone has ever done) and it was not rushed either. (I usually take over an hour just to blow dry my hair). Thank you Tracy! I will surely be a regular customer.

Out of stock of at least two advertised items.  They should know a 4 pack of HT Greek yogurt at $2 is going to sell so they should have ordered more.  Furthermore, the manager didn't even offer to substitute four loose yogurts for the same price which would make sense.  This store has gotten to be a little too busy so it's back to my regular one which I will not share or review (sorry).

column23: I wish this was my local HT. I live between two other Fort Mill HT's, but this one - being the newest - if very clean and well organized. Plus, it anchors lot of other great shops and restaurants.   You can't go wrong with it having a gas station as well right out on the main road, gotta get that VIC member three penny discount!!  I've never run into any issues with this location, they are always well stocked.   Like most Teeter's it does include a Starbucks inside.

column23: The actual grocery store is nice and well stocked. My 3 stars is for the deli part where they make sub samdwiches. I had to wait about 25 minutes to get my sandwich made tonight. There were 2 people in front of me getting sandwiches. A guy restocked the lettuce because it was empty. The new lettuce was brown. The woman named Jill who made my sandwich threw the brown lettuce out and replaced with another bag of fresh lettuce . She was in the middle of gettingy bread ready when she threw the bread in the trash for some reason and had to start over. It took my husband and I about 10-15 to get our sandwiches. We were also trying to keep our kids from acting up while we were waiting for our sandwiches. They need 2 people making sandwiches at this location because Jill is kind of slow. The sandwich was tasty though so I won't complain about that.

column23: Cozy alternative to the mainstream mass volume coffee option - with wifi  :)
Excellent... They are going to a vegitarian menu to attract more people. The service is wonderful, atmosphere is outstanding and the food is to die for... Must go

Although technically a coffee shop, this is also a wonderful Chilean restaurant; with a large selection of coffee creations (the Mexican hot chocolate is perfect).  My favorite, however, has to be the empanadas, made in the Chilean style with ground beef and black olives and served with house made pico de gallo.

Even though we have to do Burpees, I totally enjoy coming to class. One day, I will get my coordination together for all the steps, but, practice makes perfect. Definitely a way for me to change up my workout routine.

column23: I was not sure what to expect when I signed up using the web special for ilovekickboxing all I knew was I wanted to get back in shape. Dealing with the staff leading up to the opening was amazing they all love what they do so much. And also are so supportive and attentive to each persons needs! From walking thru the door on day 1 I've felt like it was a family! Class was amazing too. Definitely what I need in my life! I could feel every muscle being worked! Can't wait to continue my journey and see great results!!! Hitting the bags is really a stress reliever and the partner drills helps meet others who love kick boxing too!!

column23: Awesome place, friendly staff, excellent workout, very clean and in a great location.  Get out and get your gloves on, you'll be sure to get  in a great workout!

If I could give them no stars I would! You will pay them a hefty sum upfront and then get nothing in return but a bunch of excuses and grown men "acting" as investigators. Additionally, they try to capitalize on your situation by assuming women are too stupid to see through their dramatics and made for TV like antics! I literally had to call and email repeatedly for updates without anything shared in response. Additionally, I never got an invoice or written documentation\/evidence to show how my money was being spent. Don't waste your money on these guys...they should be embarrassed and ashamed of themselves for essentially stealing from clients who are obviously coming to them for assistance because of serious needs. Dishonorable to say the least!
Very professional staff and the work they did was top-notch. These investigators will go above and beyond for you. Especially if you are military or a veteran.

I hate to sound mean, but the movie Dumb and Dumber come to mind. If it weren't my life and my $, it would have been a comedy of errors. They are either crooked or stupid. Those are the only 2 explanations.

column23: The nickel and dime comment from Paul is spot on.  I've been sent letters and charged for cleaning siding twice and the work was done and a message left for Kuester with no return call.  I have neighbors with terrible looking yards, dirty siding, and others but they never receive a notice so this is personal for some reason.  I've always paid my dues in advance and also cut grass for a vacant house beside me regularly but they still nickel and dime.  If you have a choice STAY AWAY!  Oh yea I even took proof into show the siding was cleaned with a date stamp on the cleaning and nothing was done!

column23: Kuester is a very professional and courteous management company, We appreciate everything that Kuester Management Group has done for our board and our neighborhood

Same as Kristen, they changed address without notice and then charge late fees.  When you ask for a refund on them, they said "oh, we can't do that." They advised me to go on their website and pay immediately. Well, when you try to log in on their crappy website (that also charges a 3% fee to pay with a card), it asks for your email to send you a link to reset your password- I thought I already had one. They also approved a repair and I had a renter in there. When the renter moved out a year later, I found out they never even completed the repair!!! They I had to go back and find all the emails to prove they actually approved it and never followed through! They of course tried to blame it on the board members who out of the goodness of their hearts volunteer for a thankless job!

column23: This management company is horrible! I can't believed my annual Hoa fee goes to pay for their crappy svice. They are out to fine you and get your money, doesn't care about the interest of people in the community or their situations.  Their customer service is horrible, especially their community manager for fort mill\/Charlotte location Mary Thaxton. She is rude! She ignored your email for month and when you do talk to her, she would never let you finish your sentence and very eager to get off the phone. She does not provide genuine customer service or try to help solve your problems.  She probably only does best sitting in her office collect weekly pay check. Can't believed the board pays them to bully you with your own money and nothing you can do about it.

This is the worst property management company I have ever seen. Purchased a property in water way palms and have been trying months to get access to the gated property. They answer the phone but they can never ever get in contact with their representative at water way. They say they will call back but never do.  20 + calls and four months later still no luck. I wouldn't recommend anyone purchase a property that is run buy this horrible company...  Update.. I finally got in touch with kimber at their local office. She is great and very easy to deal with. A true asset to the company. She helped me get access to the property and boat storage. It still shouldn't have been such a nightmare to get in touch with her. My advice to the company would be to set up a welcome packet with the local office's information. Who wants to call an office to be put on old for ten min only to be put on hold again then to be told they can't get the person you need to talk to and never get a call back. My only other complaint is the current club house hours are from 8am to 12pm . I hope this time changes during spring and summer as four hours in the early part of the day is useless to most.

If you are thinking about hiring Kuester to manage your property, think again. This company will under service and overcharge you. Their management will not return phone calls if you have a complaint, but will continue to have underlings placate you with vague answers to your complaints or concerns.  If you have already hired them, you may want to revisit your contract to make sure you understand what they can do to you. You may be surprised.

Horrible company to deal with.  We live in Briarcrest in Waxhaw, NC.  I tried to get a pool clubhouse rental agreement for my son's birthday party for over five weeks.  Other people had been trying to get the same contract all summer.  Nothing.  Then, four days before the party I get fed up and start mass emailing them and posting on their facebook page.  Magically I get a response that says "sorry for the delay we were dealing with a security issue at the clubhouse" and sent me a hastily put together document.  Total lie.  The contract metadata showed it had just been created.  On top of it, they allowed the developer to illegally raise the rental rate by almost 100% on a whim and tried to play it off as it was in the best interest of the HOA when the HOA advisory committee asked on multiple times not to do that.  Also, the clubhouse HVAC was broken all summer long and they dragged their feet for months to fix it.  Why we are paying them almost $1300 a month is beyond me.  If you go with this company beware, you have been warned.

column23: If you could rate negative stars I would rate them 'minus 5'.   This outfit provides little to no value for money, does not communicate or respond to issues for any reason- even security or safety related.  This company is a do nothing fiscal drag on the community and gives HOA management a black eye

Run, fast! We could not get out from under Kuester fast enough. Being on the HOA board is difficult enough but then you throw in incompetent management and its even worse! Ben and Deb are masters at nickel and diming your association to death. We were double charged every single time we had to mail something, once in 'Postage' and once in 'Office Supplies. Whenever we asked a question pertaining to any account they would always reply, "I will have to get back to you" It became a running joke they said it so often. We used to have to send multiple emails, and when I say multiple I mean over a dozen just to get the answers we were promised. We also had so many complaints from our fellow neighbors who would call them and never get anything resolved. Kuester's reply? "We don't show any calls" I understand that some people may not always tell the truth but come on! We are talking about a good 40 different homeowners all saying the same thing..  I left the board because I moved and was so very happy not to have to deal with them again, but NO! They charged me $130 on my closing statement just to send a statement to the closing attorney showing I was up to date on my dues. How messed up is that? And I bet you they also DOUBLE  charged for the postage. Do yourself a favor and save yourself the headaches, stay FAR away from Kuester!

In my opinion, this is a very unethical, crooked management company.  I have had experience with them in two different neighborhoods.  They overcharge and are impossible to contact.  If you are able to speak with them, they will never give straight answers.  Everyone I have spoken with in my current neighborhood has had a terrible experience with Kuester and wants change.  Many homeowners decided to start attending association meetings and question what they felt like were unethical behaviors by both Kuester and the HOA board.  When Kuester found out about this, they tried to prevent owners from attending and speaking at meetings.  Members had to bring the actual bylaws to meetings and quote from them the rules that gave them the right to attend and speak.  Due to the frustration with Kuester, some homeowners posted negative reviews online.  These owners were then sent emails from Kuester threatening to sue the home owners if they did not remove the negative reviews.  Unfortunately, these home owners were unaware of their 1st Amendment right to post honest, negative reviews so they subsequently removed their posts due to fear.  It is my opinion that Kuester uses the threat of fines and lawsuits to keep home owners from taking any action against Kuester's poor management practices.  When I purchase a new home, my number one requirement will be that Kuester is not the management company.

Honestly the worst HOA management company out there.  The company changed addresses twice while overseeing our home.  They never communicated change of address and this resulted in constant issues with payments.  Furthermore, if you pay with an on-line bill pay get ready for big headaches - they overlook these payments - resulting in delinquent notices.  They have actually sent me to collections when i refused to pay late fees due.  They had my payment on time - they just didn't process on their end and then sent me to collections for the late fees!!!! Horrible, big aggravation and time sucker because they can't manage their own office!

Kuester has a bully mentality.  Stay far away from this company which comes off as being completely without wisdom and common sense.  We live in Bridgemill and have a basketball pole facing in their opinion, the wrong way. The backstory is that ten years ago we received APPROVAL from our builder who was at the time, manager of our neighborhood, to place the pole where it currently sits because had we placed it where it was supposed to be, per bylaws, it was mere feet from our good neighbor's air conditioner, Dish satellite and other sensitive exposed electricals. Can you imagine how happy he'd be with us every time a free throw hit his siding? Now ten years later, Kuester is hired to be our HOA and they are relentless that we move it. We've asked for a rep from Kuester to come out--nothing but threatening emails and mailings from them, where they stalk our property from the curb and snap creepy pics of our pole.  To add to that, we have been warned about a mailbox that needs tending to.  Memo to Kuester: Roger. Understand mailbox needs a fresh coat of spray paint. It's been a cold spring with often inclement weather on the weekends. I've got the mailbox on my to do ASAP. (Mind you we have one of the most pristine yards, beds, foliage and house facade in the neighborhood. In other words we deeply care how we present ourselves and our property and we respect our neighbors enough to keep things lovely.) Meanwhile--while Kuester is bullying me relentlessly, the communal neighborhood fencing across the street from me is falling apart and desperately needs painted. IT HAS BEEN THIS WAY SINCE KUESTER HAS MANAGED BRIDGEMILL!  Kuester--oh where oh where are you in getting this addressed? (Crickets chirping.) Oh wait--I know--they're driving around snapping creepy pictures of everyone else's problems --while letting common areas fall into severe and shabby disrepair.  Life's hard enough, run, don't walk from a Kuester managed property or neighborhood. There's a reason why they have such terrible ratings from the people they supposedly 'serve.'

Incompetent and intransparent management company.  Never reply to e-mails. Currently waiting on a reply to an e-mail sent 15 days ago despite a reminder e-mail 3 days ago.  A few other examples:  1) Received an e-mail from Kuester support not too long ago that said the following: "In recent weeks, concerns about possible criminal activity have been brought to the Board's attention. In light of these concerns, we would ask all homeowners to remain vigilant. Should you note unusual traffic or suspicious activity, we ask that you call the police."  Nothing else was in that e-mail. Would you please tell me the nature of the criminal activity so that I know what I should be looking out for? How much more vague can it get?  2) In another situation: Me: "Could you please add me to the e-mail distribution lists so that I can be sure that I receive all relevant electronic communication from Kuester. Please also send me a confirmation e-mail once I have been added to the DGs. I am worried that despite the fact that I have an online Kuester account and paid my HOA dues online I appear to be missing on certain DGs. Finally note that homeowners not receiving e-mails was something that was brought up during the annual HOA meeting held last December."  In response Kuester support says: "Thank you for your email. We were experiencing a minor "glitch" in our system which has now been corrected. We apologize for the inconvenience this may have caused you. Please let me know if you have any questions or concerns."  Now that adequately addressed my concerns in regards to not being on the DGs ... not.   During the next HOA meeting or open board meeting I will be sure to propose to replace Kuester with another management company. It cannot get worse.   P.S.: If you look at Kuester reviews on their own website you will see plenty of overall 5 star ratings: Yet on Facebook they have 3.5 and on Yelp 2.5 stars. I do wonder where that discrepancy comes from.

Best authentic Colombian restaurant in this area. I have been to all. The menu contains a broad selection of Colombian dishes that are second to none. The staff was helpful and courteous in explaining the dishes.  I was totally impressed and would recommend Casablanca Colombia to all my friends!
We love this place.  The portions are very generous and the food is delicious.  My wife always gets the grilled chicken and my son oves the columbiana soda
Fantastic.  Delicious.  The plantains were on point!  The fried pork loin was amazing!  Will definitely be back!

column23: This is the best Colombian restaurant in the area. The food is tasty and generous.  I wish they offer more Colombian food variety like  sancocho or ajIaco. On other hand, The location is hard to get to because it is far away from any interstate road.
I was so surprised to find this Colombian restaurant in the middle of nowhere but definitely worth the drive the food was awesome and the owner and his wife are very sweet people LOVE this place

Excellent experience, great food, extremely friendly service!  I stopped in for my first dining experience at Casa Columbia this week during lunch hours.  We were seated, drinks delivered and food ordered in less than 5 minutes.  I ordered the #1 special and it was phenomenal!  When the rice and beans are superb, you know you came to the right place. The plate also came with a variety of meats, an egg and some delicious plantains, as well a as a type of corn bread.  Great find that you will not be disappointed in trying!

I'm so happy this place opened in Indian Land.  We love Colombian Food. We've been here a bunch of times.  The owner is really nice and very generous.  He's given us soup and samples of his Fantastic desserts for free.  The soup is ALWAYS great and the desserts are AMAZING!  I couldn't choose which one I love best.  When we come, my favorite entree is the Mushroom Chicken.  It is superb! My son always gets the breaded steak, sweet plantains, red beans, and white rice.  My husband always gets the Number 1.  We LOVE this place, really.  It is always wonderful and so much food.  The next day, we mix every leftover into a pan, add a couple of eggs and stick it into a tortilla.  Good times!

Went for the first time after seeing on Yelp. I used to live in Florida and was spoiled with good Latin food everywhere. Food was delicious and authentic. Large portions. Owner was extremely friendly and made us feel welcome. So happy to have found this gem in our backyard in Indian Land. We will be regulars.

Colombian Food just wasn't on our radar, so it took us a while to try Casa Colombia on Highway 521 in Fort Mill.  My husband and I decided to go tonight.  It was wonderful!  I had the breaded steak, sweet plantains, red beans, and white rice.  My husband had the number 1.  They were Fabulous!  Before our entrees, we had salad and pea soup.  Both were great but, the pea soup was excellent. Neither one of us has had pea soup in years.  It was really delicious with just enough kick.  You could tell it was made with fresh ingredients.  The owner and chef was kind enough to give us some to bring home.  We can't wait to have it for lunch.  I highly recommend this place and will most definitely be back.

Really liked this place a lot. I got the #5, I believe, and really enjoyed it. It came with a beef broth soup with rice and potatoes, and that was probably one of my favorite things. The plantains were really tasty, too. They also have a cilantro lime type of sauce that went great with pretty much everything. We got flan for desert, and it was awesome. More like a cheesecake texture than what is normally served, but that's my preference. For the money, you get a ton of food.   Super strange for a restaurant like this to exist in Indian Land, but all the better. I'll definitely recommend this place to my friends.

column23: The food is fresh, amazing and tastes like it was made with such love and care! The restaurant is so cozy and the owners are the sweetest and most caring people I've met in ages. My wife and I loved it and will be back all the time!!!!!!

This place was ridiculous. The waitress had no idea what was going on. I guess that's ok since she was new. But no one took responsibility or tried to reasonably rectify the situation. The food tasted awful. Half our order was forgotten, and the list goes on and on and on and on as to how poorly this place is run. Definitely won't be returning here.

The service was amazing! The owner came out and greeted us personally and waited on us. Truly amazing Colombia food. We traveled all the way from mint hill because we have tried almost every Colombian restaurant in the charlotte area and haven't found one that really spoke to us. This truly tastes like grandmas food and that's what we are looking for In a Colombian restaurant, apart from feeing at home with the exceptional service we were given. You have to try this hidden gem! And don't forget to ask for the plantains!

What an unexpected pleasure.  Great food and large serving size.  The owner was very involved, he even made a great suggestion for preparing my leftovers the next day.   I tried the typical Columbian dinner with some carne asida, red sausage, avocado, pork back, an egg, sweet plantains, rice, beans, and traditional Columbian corn bread. Tres Leches for desert.  I will be back.
